article.headline: Radford 96, High Point 76
article.story: RADFORD, Va. (AP) -- Chris Oliver scored 25 and Dan Ross added 23 off seven 3-pointers as Radford snapped High Point's three-game win streak with a 96-76 victory Wednesday night. Ross had five 3-pointers in the first half as Radford (9-7, 2-2 Big South Conference) took a 40-31 lead at halftime. The Panthers (10-5, 3-2) went 4-of-14 from the floor during the first 10 minutes of the second half, and Radford capitalized, building a 29-point lead with 7:20 remaining. Oliver scored 20 during a 27-7 run. High Point closed to within 13 with 1:08 left, but could get no closer. Radford had 12 steals, leading to 17 Panthers turnovers. Whit Holcomb-Faye scored 14 for Radford, and Kenny Thomas added 10. Akeem Scott sank four from 3-point range to lead High Point with 21 points and Arizona Reid had his third consecutive double-double with 18 points and 12 rebounds.
